Elm Cottage July 19th /68
Winnie, my dear;
Have you forgotten all about your Auntie Mary, that used to hold you, and sing to you, and love you almost to death? If you have, I'm sorry - but if your little memory is filled up with other good things tis all right - Your ma - says, you say, you are going to be a minister - That's right - Your Auntie looks forward, gladly, to some fair bright Sabbath morning, when the bells will ring so clearly, and softly, and call her to church, where the deep - toned organ will give the sweetest harmony, and the church will be filled with people, and her dear, darling, Winnie, will stand in the pulpit and read sweet hymns, with his musical voice, and preach and pray - Wont that be nice? O, yes indeed ! And you are making a bed-quilt - Now, you ask your mamma to send a pattern of the pieces you sew, and I'll send a piece of the dress I used to wear when you was a baby - Will you ? yours lovingly Auntie Mary
